   "source": [
    "# Wildfire Burn-Scar Severity Mapping — Model Evaluation\n",
    "**ENSF-617 | Group 40**  \n",
    "Aparna Ayyalasomayajula · Radadiya Mansi Mukesh Bhai  \n",
    "Department of Electrical and Software Engineering, University of Calgary\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "This notebook presents the complete evaluation of four U-Net-based segmentation architectures trained for multi-class wildfire burn-severity mapping from Sentinel-2 multitemporal imagery.  \n",
    "All metrics are computed on a temporally held-out test set (2022–2023 fires; 1,047 patches from 12 fires).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Evaluation covers:**\n",
    "1. Dataset & split summary  \n",
    "2. Overall model comparison (mIoU, mDice, PR-AUC)  \n",
    "3. Training dynamics  \n",
    "4. Per-class performance analysis  \n",
    "5. Confusion matrix analysis  \n",
    "6. Precision–Recall curves  \n",
    "7. Per-fire performance  \n",
    "8. Ablation study  \n",
    "9. Baseline comparison  \n",
    "10. Qualitative predictions (ResUNet)  "
   ]
  },
